&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NORTH WALES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; COMMUNITY DENTAL SERVICE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFIED DENTAL NURSE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based at Flint Clinic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO MATERNITY COVER&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a qualified Dental Nurse who enjoys variety and is looking for a fresh challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, self-motivated Dental Nurse to join our dental team who can relate to all age groups and who can assist the clinicians with a full range of dental procedures. Experience of patients with special care is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a qualified Dental Nurse you will be based at Flint Dental Clinic. The successful candidate must be willing to provide dental nursing support in satellite clinics, mobile units, hospital venues and on a domiciliary basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to travel between sites in a timely manner is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be registered with the General Dental Council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 10/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
